1.Basics of entrepreneurship. Main concepts regarding enterprises and business operation. Supply and demand, competition types, financial reports, financing, shares, dividends, budget, taxes, specific characters of high-technology companies. 
2. Composition of biotechnology companies. Company structure, departments, professions and their educational background, management, board, scientific board, leadership, specificity of high-technology (biotechnology) companies. 
3. Biotechnology in the world and in Estonia, biotechnology and state. Overview of Biotechnology companies. Biotech and pharma. Trends. Comparison of companies in EU and USA. Overview of Estonian and EU policy on biotechnology. Governmental support to young companies. 
4. From idea to company. Practical hints how to establish company. Business plan. Sources for financing. 
5. Product development, Quality systems, Project and time management.
6. Sales and Marketing. Targeting, sales process, international trade, negotiations. 
7. Intellectual property. Types, process, cost, IP management, licensing, IP in company's strategy, IP databases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Aim of the lecture is to give an overview of possibilities of entrepreneurship in biotechnology, the practical hints how to establish a company, compile business plan, find finances, protect intellectual property and find personnel. Lecturers will give also overview of the Estonian and World Biotechnology Sector.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student, who has passed the course; 1.Knows the main concepts regarding enterprises and business operation. 2.Understands connections and essence of different areas in small enterprises (Research and development, production and services, sales and marketing, personnel, financial management and leadership). 3.Have basic understanding how to prepare a business plan. 4.Understand the specificity of high-technology companies. 5.Have an overview of biotechnology sector in Estonia and trends in the world. 6.Have basic knowledge how to establish company and have an overview of supporting institutions. 7.Knows the intellectual property protection possibilities and the process, enables to evaluate the role of IP in the enterprise and is able to make simple patent searches
